OL,3,CStates of Guernsey votes to pave the
OL,4,Cway for GST
OL,6,FGuernsey's politicians have voted
OL,7,Ftoday (6 November 2024) - for the
OL,8,Ffirst time - to potentially introduce
OL,9,Fa Goods and Services Tax in the island.
OL,11,FThe proposed amendment to Guernsey's
OL,12,F2025 budget, voted through by
OL,13,Fdeputies, would see the income tax
OL,14,Frate rise from 20% to 22% for two
OL,15,Fyears and "develop systems, processes
OL,16,Fand legislation" for GST.
OL,18,FHowever, politicians still have to
OL,19,Fvote through the overall budget to
OL,20,Fofficially introduce these changes.
